By the Holy Spirit , and Jesus Christ: 
\par }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [Rom 8:15-17]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  For ye have not received the spirit of bondage again to fear; but ye have received the Spirit of adoption, whereby we cry, Abba, Father. }{
\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{16\}}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  The Spirit itself beareth witness with our spirit, that we are the children of God: }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{17\}}{
\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  And if children, then heirs; heirs of God, and joint-heirs with Christ; if so be that we suffer with him, that we may be also glorified together. 
\par }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [John 1:10-15]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  He was in the world, and the world was made by him, and the world knew him not. }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{11\}}{
\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  He came unto his own, and his own received him not. }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{12\}}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 
 But as many as received him, to them gave he power to become the sons of God, even to them that believe on his name: }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{13\}}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 
 Which were born, not of blood, nor of the will of the flesh, nor of the will of man, but of God. }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{14\}}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  And the 
Word was made flesh, and dwelt among us, (and we beheld his glory, the glory as of the only begotten of the Father,) full of grace and truth. 
\par }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [John 1:18]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  No man hath seen God at any time; the only begotten Son, which is in the bosom of the Father, he hath declared him. 
\par }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [John 16:14-15]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  He }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [i.e.. God the Father]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 
 shall glorify me: for he shall receive of mine, and shall show it unto you. }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{15\}}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 
 All things that the Father hath are mine: therefore said I, that he shall take of mine, and shall show it unto you. 
\par }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [Gal 4:4-7]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  But when the fulness of the time was come, God sent forth his Son, made of a woman, made under the law, }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{5\}}{
\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  To redeem them that were under the law, that we might receive the adoption of sons. }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{6\}}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 
 And because ye are sons, God hath sent forth the Spirit of his Son into your hearts, crying, Abba, Father. }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{7\}}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 
 Wherefore thou art no more a servant, but a son; and if a son, then an heir of God through Christ. 
\par The only way to appropriate the knowledge of God the Father is to act as a Son, as His Son, J
esus Christ showed us. Then, the Spirit of God enlightens us. So we must see that IF we call God our Father, we are making a solemn pledge to live a moral life according to our Father's commandments. As we struggle to live according to the commandments, o
ur soul is made capable of enlightenment concerning God by degrees. 
