\par How should we understand the terms "heaven" and "earth"? 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid6452859 \b\fs48\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning36\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid6452859 \~{\*\bkmkstart a22}
{\*\bkmkend a22}ANSWER 22
\par }\pard\plain \s52\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid6452859 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 
Scripture uses heaven to denote three things. 
\par }{\b\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 The sky and stars, also known as the "firmament": }{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 
\par }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [Psa 103:11]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  For as the heaven is high above the earth, so great is his mercy toward them that fear him. 
\par [Duet 17:3] And hath gone and served other gods, and worshipped them, either the sun, or moon, or any of the host of heaven, which I have not commanded; 
\par }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [Jer 31:37]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  Thus sai
th the LORD; If heaven above can be measured, and the foundations of the earth searched out beneath, I will also cast off all the seed of Israel for all that they have done, saith the LORD. 
\par }{\b\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 Salvation, the state of the soul when it is purified and has spiritual knowledge of God. In this context, Heaven is a condition, not a place per se.}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  
\par }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [Mat 3:1-2]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  In those days came John the Baptist, preaching in the wilderness of Judaea, }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{2\}}{
\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  And saying, Repent ye: for the kingdom of heaven is at hand. 
\par [2 Cor 12:2-4] I knew a man in Christ above fourteen years ago, (whether in the body, I cannot tell; or whether out of the body, I cannot tell: God knoweth;) such an one caught up to the third heaven. }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{3\}}{
\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  And I knew such a man, (whether in the body, or out of the body, I cannot tell: God knoweth;) }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{4\}}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 
 How that he was caught up into paradise, and heard unspeakable words, which it is not lawful for a man to utter. 
\par [2 Cor 5:1] For we know that if our earthly house of this tabernacle were dissolved, we have a building of God, an house not made with hands, eternal in the heavens 
\par }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [Acts 7:55-56]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  But he, being full of the Holy Ghost, looked up stedfastly into heaven, and saw the glory of God, and Jesus standing on the right hand of God, }{
\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{56\}}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  And said, Behold, I see the heavens opened, and the Son of man standing on the right hand of God. 
\par }{\b\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 The Spiritual, invisible world, of the Angels.}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  
\par }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [Psa 33:6]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  By the word of the LORD were the heavens made; and all the host of them by the breath of his mouth. 
\par (The "Host" is another word for the Angels,}{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  [Luke 2:13]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  And suddenly there was with the angel a multitude of the heavenly host praising God ...") 
\par [Dan 4:35] And all the inhabitants of the earth are reputed as nothing: and he doeth according to his will in the army of heaven, and among the inhabitants of the earth: and none can stay his hand, or say unto him, What doest thou? 
\par }{\b\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 Earth can have a spiritual and physical meaning. }{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 
\par }{\b\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 It can denote the land: }{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 
\par }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [Gen 1:6-10]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  And God said, Let there be a firmament in the midst of the waters, and let it divide the waters from the waters. }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{
7\}}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  And God made the firmament, and divided the waters which were under the firmament from the waters which were above the firmament: and it was so. }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{8\}}{
\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  And God called the firmament Heaven. And the evening and the morning were the second day. }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{9\}}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 
 And God said, Let the waters under the heaven be gathered together unto one place, and let the dry land appear: and it was so. }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{10\}}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  And God called the dry land E
arth; and the gathering together of the waters called he Seas: and God saw that it was good. 
\par }{\b\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 It can denote the entire visible world: }{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 
\par }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [Gen 1:1]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  In the beginning God created the heaven and the earth. 
\par }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [Heb 1:10-12]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  And, Thou, Lord, in the beginning hast laid the foundation of the earth; and the heavens are the works of thine hands: }{
\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{11\}}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  They shall perish; but thou remainest; and they all shall wax old as doth a garment; }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{12\}}{
\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  And as a vesture shalt thou fold them up, and they shall be changed: but thou art the same, and thy years shall not fail. 
\par }{\b\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 Knowledge that is available to all (not spiritual knowledge, which is only for the elect, who are pure): }{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 
\par }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [John 3:12-13]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  If I have told you earthly things, and ye believe not, how shall ye believe, if I tell you of heavenly things? }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{
13\}}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  And no man hath ascended up to heaven, but he that came down from heaven, even the Son of man which is in heaven. 
\par }{\b\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 It can also denote the sinful condition of carnality and worldliness:}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  
\par }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [John 3:31]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  He that cometh from above is above all: he that is of the earth is earthly, and speaketh of the earth: he that cometh from heaven is above all. 
\par [Phil 3:19] Whose end is destruction, whose God is their belly, and whose glory is in their shame, who mind earthly things.) 
\par }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [James 3:13-17]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  Who is a wise man and endued with knowledge among you? let him show out of a good conversation his works with meekness of wisdom. }{
\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{14\}}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  But if ye have bitter envying and strife in your hearts, glory not, and lie not against the truth. }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{15\}}{
\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  This wisdom descendeth not from above, but is earthly, sensual, devilish. }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{16\}}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 
 For where envying and strife is, there is confusion and every evil work. }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{17\}}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 
 But the wisdom that is from above is first pure, then peaceable, gentle, and easy to be entreated, full of mercy and good fruits, without partiality, and without hypocrisy. 
\par }{\b\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 It can also denote the flesh, that is, our bodies: }{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 
\par [2 Cor 5:1] For we know that if our earthly house of this tabernacle were dissolved, we have a building of God, an house not made with hands, eternal in the heavens. 
\par }{\i\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 In the context of the Symbol of Faith}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 , "Heaven" refers to the invisible world, and "earth" to the visible world. 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid6452859 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs32\insrsid11615387\charrsid6291830 
