Besides the First reference in Genesis, how does the OT speak of the Holy Trinity? 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid6452859 \b\fs48\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning36\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid6452859 ANSWER 28
\par }\pard\plain \s52\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid6452859 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 
The Appearance of the Three Angels to Abraham is understood as a "type" of the Holy Trinity: 
\par }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [Gen 18:2-4]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  And he lift up his eyes and looked, and, lo
, three men stood by him: and when he saw them, he ran to meet them from the tent door, and bowed himself toward the ground, }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{3\}}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 
 And said, My Lord, if now I have found favor in thy sight, pass not away, I pray thee, from thy servant: }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{4\}}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  Let a little water
, I pray you, be fetched, and wash your feet, and rest yourselves under the tree: 
\par The three angels were not the Holy Trinity itself, but pointed to this dogma, as in a riddle. 
\par A type is an event (such as the passage of the Jews through the Red Sea) or object (such as Joshua, or the ark of Noah) which explains a dogma in a mystical way, and/or prophesies a future event. 
\par The passage of the Jews through the Red Sea describes baptism, and prophesies its necessity for the church. 
\par Joshua, also rendered "Jesus" whose name means "Savior", is a type of Christ. 
\par Two passages in Genesis have God referring to Himself in the plural: 
\par }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [Gen 1:26]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  And God said, Let us make man in our image, after our likeness: and let them have dominion over the fish of the sea, and ove
r the fowl of the air, and over the cattle, and over all the earth, and over every creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth. 
\par }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [Gen 3:22]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  And the LORD God said, Behold, the man is become as one of us, to know good and evil: and now, lest he put forth his
 hand, and take also of the tree of life, and eat, and live for ever: 
\par Isaiah's vision, with its repetition of "Holy", darkly refers to the Holy Trinity: 
\par }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [Isa 6:3]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  And one cried unto another, and said, Holy, holy, holy, is the LORD of hosts: the whole earth is full of his glory. 
\par Perhaps the following passages are the most clear of all OT references to the Holy Trinity: 
\par }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [Isa 11:2-3]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  And the spirit of the LORD shall rest upon him, the spirit of wisdom and understanding, the spirit of counsel and might, the
 spirit of knowledge and of the fear of the LORD; }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 \{3\}}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 
 And shall make him of quick understanding in the fear of the LORD: and he shall not judge after the sight of his eyes, neither reprove after the hearing of his ears: 
\par }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [Isa 42:1]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  Behold my servant, whom I uphold; mine elect, in whom my soul delighteth; I have put my spirit upon him: he shall bring forth judgment to the Gentiles. 
\par }{\cs54\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830 [Isa 48:16]}{\fs32\insrsid6452859\charrsid6291830  Come ye near unto me, hear ye this; I have not spoken in secret from the beginning; from the time that it was, ther
e am I: and now the Lord GOD, and his Spirit, hath sent me. 
\par ( See also: Isaiah 61:1-3 ; Isaiah 63:9,10 ) 
